## ğŸ§© LeetCode 37 â€” Sudoku Solver  

### ğŸ” Problem Statement  
Write a program to solve a 9x9 Sudoku puzzle by filling empty cells.  
Each row, column, and 3x3 sub-box must contain digits 1â€“9 without repetition.

---

### ğŸ’¡ Approach  
- Used **Backtracking** to fill cells one by one.  
- For each empty cell (`.`), try digits `'1'` to `'9'`.  
- Validate placement with an `issafe()` function checking:
  - Row  
  - Column  
  - 3x3 sub-grid  
- If valid, recursively move forward.  
- If stuck, backtrack and try next digit.  

---

### ğŸ§  Key Idea  
A Sudoku can be viewed as a **constraint satisfaction problem**, where each move must satisfy Sudoku rules before proceeding.

---

### ğŸ§© Code â€” `sudoku_solver.cpp`
```cpp
class Solution {
public:

bool issafe(vector<vector<char>>& board,int row,int col,char dig){
   //horigontal
   for(int i=0;i<9;i++){
    if(board[row][i]==dig)
    return false;
   }
   //vertical
    for(int j=0;j<9;j++){
    if(board[j][col]==dig)
    return false;
   }

   //grid
    int srow=(row/3)*3;
    int scol=(col/3)*3;
    for(int i=srow;i<=srow+2;i++){
        for(int j=scol;j<=scol+2;j++){
            if(board[i][j]==dig){
                return false;
            }
        }
    }
    return true;
}

bool helper(vector<vector<char>>& board,int row,int col){
    if(row==9){
        return true;
    }
    int nextrow=row,nextcolumn=col+1;
    if(nextcolumn==9){
        nextrow+=1;
        nextcolumn=0;
    }
    if(board[row][col] != '.'){
      return helper(board,nextrow,nextcolumn);
    }
    for(char i='1';i<='9';i++){
        if(issafe(board,row,col,i)){
            board[row][col]=i;
             if(helper(board,nextrow,nextcolumn)){
                return true;
             }
              board[row][col]='.';
        }
    }
    return false;
}
    void solveSudoku(vector<vector<char>>& board) {
        helper(board,0,0);
    }
};
